“Regression”
by Joseph Egbulefu
joseph[dot]egbulefu[at]gmail[dot]com


Library for various regression methods: currently linear, polynomial, local regression, and robust local regression. Compilation requires boost(http://www.boost.org/) and  Rcpp (http://www.rcpp.org/) header files. Rcpp is used to aid testing. Rcpp enables easier generation of random inputs for testing and evaluation of output of fitting against R’s building regression fits.


Can compile LocalRegression.cpp with gcc as (on MacOSX for example):
$ g++ -std=c++11 -c LocalRegression.cpp  -I/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Resources/include -DNDEBUG  -I/usr/local/include -I/opt/X11/include   -I/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.1/Resources/library/Rcpp/include  -O3 -pedantic


Linking requires lapack and blas libraries, along with Rcpp linking procedures (http://www.rcpp.org/). On Mac OSX unit:
$ R CMD SHLIB -o libreg.so TestSet.o Regression.o LinearRegression.o PolyRegression.o LOESSRegression.o RLOESSRegression.o -L/usr/local/lib -llapack -L/usr/local/lib -lblas -L/usr/local/gfortran/lib -lgfortran  -O3 -pedantic


